{"lemma":"فَسادُ","slug":"فَسادُ","root":"ف.س.د","root_slug":"ف-س-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-س-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَساد","root":"فسد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33855"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَسَدَ (fasada) (form I).","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"corruption","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَبْغِ ٱلْفَسَادَ فِي ٱلْأَرْضِ؛ إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ لَا يُحِبُّ ٱلْمُفْسِدِينَ.","english":"and seek not corruption in the earth; lo! Allah loveth not corrupters"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rottenness, spoiledness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"depravity, wickedness"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.saːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33855","headword_ar":"فَسَادٌ","root":"fsd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of 1: (S, M, A, &c.:) or a simple subst.: (Msb:) [as a subst. signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Badness, evilness, corruptness, unsoundness, wrongness, wrongfulness, impropriety, unrighteousness, wickedness, vitiousness, depravity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishonesty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being devoid of virtue"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efficacy; a corrupted, vitiated, perverted, marred, spoiled, deteriorated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tainted, state; a state of disorder"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disturbance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of destruction, annihilation, consumption, waste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, PS, &c.:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAHN","text_ar":"صَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, M, Msb.) And it is also [frequently used as a quasi-inf. n.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifosaAdN","text_ar":"اـِفْسَادٌ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2397},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendering, bad, evil, corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (see 4:) and, oftener, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting ill, corruptly, wrong, wrongfully, improperly, unrighteously, wickedly, vitiously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishonestly; doing evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exciting, disorder, disturbance, disagreement, discord, dissension, strife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarrelling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (L:) and [particularly] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking property wrongfully."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harobu AlfasaAdi","text_ar":"حَرْبُ الفَسَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war of evildoing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: thus was termed a war that happened between [the two sub-tribes]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw$k","text_ar":"بَنُوشك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which the latter word is app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibokK","text_ar":"شِبْكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawov","text_ar":"غَوْث"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the tribe of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaY~i'","text_ar":"طَىِّء"},{"kind":"text","text":": it was so termed because one party patched their sandals with the cars of the other, and one party drank wine out of the skulls of the other. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Drought, barrenness, dearth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scarcity of good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) so in the Kur [xxx. 40],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahara A@lofasaAdu","text_ar":"ظَهَرَ ا@لْفَسَادُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Albar~i wa A@lobaHori","text_ar":"فِى البَرِّ وَ ا@لْبَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath appeared in the land, and in the cities that are upon the rivers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, TA;) accord. to Zj; (M;) or accord. to Ez-Zejjájee. (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","L","M","K"]}]}}